# Code owners — review-required paths.
#
# GitHub matches paths against a single CODEOWNERS line per file (last match
# wins). Owners listed here automatically become required reviewers when a PR
# touches the matched path, regardless of who opened it.
#
# Today this is mostly symbolic — solo project, single owner. Once a second
# committer joins this stops being theatre and starts gating real reviews.
# Keep the list focused on security-sensitive surfaces.

# ---- security-critical: service-role bypasses RLS ----
# Any expansion of the service-role allowlist or change to the client factory
# itself must be reviewed by the repo owner. The whole point of the allowlist
# is that aspiration drift past five entries is a smell — see
# `scripts/verify-service-role-usage.mjs` soft-cap.
/scripts/verify-service-role-usage.mjs   @grufio
/lib/supabase/service-role.ts            @grufio

# ---- security-critical: env-var helpers ----
# `getRequiredEnv` and friends govern how secrets are read. A change here
# affects every server-side bootstrap path.
/lib/env.ts                              @grufio

# ---- security-critical: error-ingest endpoint ----
# Receives client-reported error payloads. Misconfigured rate-limits or
# data-exposure rules here would leak request shapes to anyone with the URL.
/app/api/errors/ingest/route.ts          @grufio

# ---- DB migration & schema ----
# Schema changes ship state to production. Reviewer signs off on the
# migration *and* the corresponding `db/schema.sql` update.
/supabase/migrations/                    @grufio
/db/schema.sql                           @grufio

# ---- CI / gate scripts ----
# Changing the gate is changing what we believe before we ship. Reviewer
# verifies that no checks have been silently weakened or removed.
/scripts/                                @grufio
/.github/workflows/                      @grufio
